== Chimichurri ==

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel @sweet potatoes{12%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Cut kernels from a @corn on the cob{1} cob. Halve and peel @red onion{1}, then cut into ⅓-inch-thick slices. Mince @garlic{1%clove} (we sent more). Mince @chili pepper{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Finely chop @cilantro{1/2%ounce}. Halve @lemon{1} and @lime{1}. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce}.

Toss sweet potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and a large pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until browned and slightly crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Set aside 1 TBSP cilantro for garnish, then combine remaining cilantro, @cumin{1/2%tsp} (we sent more), @olive oil{3%tbsp}, a pinch of garlic, chili (to taste), and a squeeze of lemon in a #small bowl{}. Season generously with salt, pepper, and more garlic and lemon (to taste).

== Charred Corn and Roasted Onion ==

Toss onion on another baking sheet with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast in oven until just starting to soften, about ~{5%minutes}, then add corn to same sheet. Return to oven and continue roasting until both are just beginning to char, about ~{7%minutes} more.

== Steak ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season @skirt steak{12%ounce} all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{2-4%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and let rest ~{5%minutes} before thinly slicing against the grain.

== Salad ==

Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1}, then cut into cubes. Add to a #medium bowl{} along with corn, onion, sweet potatoes, tomatoes, reserved cilantro, a squeeze of lime, and any remaining chili (to taste). Season with salt and pepper. Divide salad and steak between plates. Drizzle with chimichurri and serve.

> Chimichurri is Argentina's version of pesto. It's herby, garlicky, and a delight to drizzle over just about anything—especially a nice piece of beef. And speaking of beef, you'll be searing up a skirt steak, which is prized for its robust, deep flavor. With a jumble of roasted sweet potatoes, corn, avocado, and tomatoes on the side, it's got the perfect balance of colorful veggie wholesomeness and luxuriant, meaty decadence.